.TH INSTALL-AZURECLIENT 1 "November 2025" "Noble Factor" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Install-AzureClient \- Install the Azure CLI on Debian-based systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Install-AzureClient
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Install-AzureClient
is a script to download and install the Azure CLI on Debian-based Linux systems. It checks for an existing installation and verifies the system type before proceeding.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , --help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR --force
Force reinstallation of Azure CLI even if it is already installed. Without this option, the script will exit successfully if Azure CLI is detected.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Must be run on a Debian-based system (checks for /etc/debian_version).
